Larissa Industries Inc said it filedwith the Securities and Exchange Commission for an initialpublic offering of two mln shares of common.    All of the shares are being sold by Larissa, which makesand markets component assemblies used in automobiles, lighttrucks, vans, helicopters and other military vehicles and innucelar reactors for the U.S. Navy submarines and othervessels.    The offering will be underwritten by Merrill Lynch CapitalMarkets and E.F. Hutton and Co Inc. Reuter&#3;